Package: nciusual
Title: NCI Method for Estimating Usual Dietary Intake Distributions
Version: 0.4.0
Authors@R: person("Conor", "McGovern", email = "comcgovern@example.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: R port of the National Cancer Institute (NCI) MIXTRAN, DISTRIB,
    and INDIVINT SAS macros for estimating usual dietary intake distributions
    from 24-hour dietary recall data. Supports amount-only models (for
    ubiquitously consumed nutrients) and two-part correlated/uncorrelated models
    (for episodically consumed foods). Offers a choice of probability sub-model
    engine (MASS::glmmPQL or lme4::glmer) and correlated-model engine (profile
    likelihood over rho or Gauss-Hermite quadrature) for the two-part model.
    Includes individual BLUP predictions via indivint(), bivariate usual intake
    and ratio estimation via distrib_bivariate(), helpers for NHANES multi-cycle
    survey weight pooling, and adaptive Gauss-Hermite quadrature utilities.
    Designed for use with NHANES data and complex survey designs.
